3 SAVING THE PROGRAM


Since AR uses FDOS it is necessary to format the disk which you 

wish use

SF"DISK NAME"

will format the disk i FDOS mode

SA"NAME"

saves the program in memory 

SD"NAME"

deletes the selected program

SM"NAME",START END

saves part of the memory ( dont EXCEED 940 KB )

SS"NAME",channel list ( 1 - 4 ) 

save sound sample in one of four channels 


------------------------------------------------------------------

4 RE LOADING A PROGRAM

LD

shows dir of FDOS disk

LR"NAME"

reloads and runs selected program

LA"NAME"

reloads program but it will not run it

LM"NAME",START

reload saved memory at start address


