6 MONITOR COMMANDS 


A ADDRESS 

assemble directly

B 

shows settings of breakpoints

BS ADDRESS

puts breakpoint at the chosen address

BD ADDRESS

clears breakpoint at the chosen address 

C cipher

disassemble the copper list at given address 

cipher 1 or 2 

D ADDRESS

disassamble the 68000

G ADDRESS

continue the interrupted program at the given address

H channel (1-4)

replay current sound

I START END TARGET 

copies the given memory area to target address

J SPRITE NO

look at and edit sprite 

M ADDRESS

shows and lets you edit the memory

N ADDRESS

show memory as text

O string START END 

fill the entire memory area

R reg value

show edit CPU register

V START END TARGET

compares memory location

W register number

show edit CIA register

Y ADDRESS

shows memory as binary

Z 

shows current options

ZD (0/1)

set drive

ZM (0/1)

activate or deactivate th memory

ZV (0/1)

activate or deactivate the virus test

ZF (0/1)

expansion ON or OFF

?

calculation command


